GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.B. 10
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE BILL DRS35008-NE-9A
Short Title: Mobile Drivers Licenses. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Hanig and Moffitt (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REQUIRING THE DIVISION OF MOTOR VEHICLES TO PROVIDE MOBILE
3 DRIVERS LICENSES UPON REQUEST, EXTENDING RECIPROCITY TO MOBILE
4 DRIVERS LICENSES ISSUED BY OTHER STATES, REQUIRING LAW
5 ENFORCEMENT OFFICERS TO UNDERGO TRAINING TO ENSURE APPROPRIATE
6 INTERACTIONS WITH MOBILE DRIVERS LICENSE HOLDERS, AND CLARIFYING
7 THAT A MOBILE DRIVERS LICENSE SATISFIES THE IN-PERSON VOTING PHOTO
8 IDENTIFICATION REQUIREMENT.
9 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
10 SECTION 1. G.S. 20-7(m1) reads as rewritten:
11 "(m1) Mobile Drivers License. – Upon request of an applicant for whom a valid license
12 exists or is issued, the Commissioner may shall issue a mobile drivers license as a supplement to
13 the valid license. A Unless otherwise provided by law, a mobile drivers license is the legal
14 equivalent of a valid license.license, for any purpose, including identification."
15 SECTION 2. Article 1A of Chapter 20 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
16 a new section to read:
17 "§ 20-4.13. Mobile drivers licenses.
18 The Commissioner shall extend reciprocity to a mobile drivers license issued by another state
19 if the license was issued subject to requirements substantially similar to the requirements for
20 mobile drivers license issuance in this State."
21 SECTION 3. G.S. 17C-6 reads as rewritten:
22 "§ 17C-6. Powers of Commission.
23 (a) In addition to powers conferred upon the Commission elsewhere in this Article, the
24 Commission shall have the following powers, which shall be enforceable through its rules and
25 regulations, certification procedures, or the provisions of G.S. 17C-10:
26 …
27 (14) Establish minimum standards for in-service training for criminal justice
28 officers. In-service training standards for sworn law enforcement officers shall
29 include all of the following training topics:
30 …
31 j. Training to ensure appropriate interactions with mobile drivers license
32 holders.
33 …."
34 SECTION 4. G.S. 17E-4 reads as rewritten:
35 "§ 17E-4. Powers and duties of the Commission.
*DRS35008-NE-9A*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (a) The Commission shall have the following powers, duties, and responsibilities, which
2 are enforceable through its rules and regulations, certification procedures, or the provisions of
3 G.S. 17E-8 and G.S. 17E-9:
4 …
5 (11) Establish minimum standards for in-service training for justice officers.
6 In-service training standards for sworn law enforcement officers shall include
7 all of the following training topics:
8 …
9 j. Training to ensure appropriate interactions with mobile drivers license
10 holders.
11 …."
12 SECTION 5. G.S. 163-166.16 reads as rewritten:
13 "§ 163-166.16. Requirement for photo identification to vote in person.
14 (a) Photo Identification Required to Vote. – When a registered voter presents to vote in
15 person, the registered voter shall produce any of the following forms of identification that contain
16 a photograph of the registered voter:
17 (1) Any of the following that is valid and unexpired, or has been expired for one
18 year or less:
19 a. A North Carolina drivers license.license, including a mobile drivers
20 license as defined in G.S. 20-4.01.
21 …."
22 SECTION 6. The Division of Motor Vehicles of the Department of Transportation
23 may contract with a qualified vendor or vendors to develop and implement the mobile drivers
24 license system mandated by G.S. 20-7(m1), as modified by this act. The Division shall adopt
25 rules implementing the requirements of this section. No later than October 1, 2025, the Division
26 shall do all of the following:
27 (1) Develop and implement a public awareness program to inform the general
28 public about the availability, functionality, and security of mobile drivers
29 licenses.
30 (2) In conjunction with the North Carolina School of Government and the
31 Department of Public Safety, develop and implement a training program
32 designed to ensure law enforcement officers are appropriately equipped for
33 interactions with mobile drivers license holders. At minimum, the training
34 shall address the protections afforded by the United States and North Carolina
35 Constitutions and how those protections relate to mobile drivers licenses. This
36 training shall be made available to both State and local government law
37 enforcement officers no later than January 1, 2026.
38 (3) Notify the State Board of Elections, the Department of Public Safety, and the
39 Secretary of State of the pendency of mobile drivers licenses.
40 (4) Consult with the federal Transportation Security Administration throughout
41 the development and implementation of the mobile drivers license system to
42 ensure mobile drivers licenses comply with all federal laws and regulations.
43 SECTION 7. Sections 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 of this act become effective July 1, 2026. The
44 remainder of this act is effective when it becomes law.
